# ============================================================
# POLYCARDS — CURSOR AGENT RULES v4.0
# Project: Flashcard app for language learning
# Stack: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
# Backend: Supabase | Deploy: Vercel
# Author: djdehoon | Repo: github.com/djdehoon/polycards-next
# ============================================================

## 🎯 PROJECT CONTEXT
You are building "PolyCards" — a flashcard app for language learners.
Users study vocabulary using Spaced Repetition (SM-2 algorithm).
The app has 100 Ukrainian words in 10 decks, stored in Supabase.
Stack: Next.js 14 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Supabase + polycards.
Current version: v0.2.7 (Theories page: /theories)
Next: Block 7 (Polish + responsive)

## 🗄️ DATABASE (Supabase)
Tables:
- public.decks        (id, slug, title, sort_order)
- public.words        (id, deck_id, term, translation, sort_order)
- public.user_progress (id, user_id, word_id, ease_factor, interval_days, next_review_at)
- public.sessions     (id, user_id, date, cards_studied) ← Block 6

Auth: Supabase Auth (email + password)
RLS: Enabled on user_progress (user sees only their own rows)

## 🏗️ ARCHITECTURE RULES

### Next.js App Router (STRICT)
- ALWAYS use App Router (src/app/) — NEVER use pages/ directory
- Server Components by default — only add "use client" when necessary
- Use Server Actions for form submissions — NOT API routes for simple forms
- API routes only for: external webhooks, complex server logic
- Use Next.js metadata API for SEO — NOT next/head
- Use next/image for ALL images — NEVER <img> tags
- Use next/link for ALL internal navigation — NEVER <a> tags

### TypeScript (STRICT)
- ALWAYS use TypeScript — never plain JavaScript
- No "any" types — use proper interfaces
- All shared types go in src/types/index.ts
- Prefer interfaces over type aliases for objects

### Supabase (STRICT)
- Use @supabase/ssr package — NOT deprecated auth-helpers
- Browser client: src/lib/supabase/client.ts
- Server client: src/lib/supabase/server.ts
- NEVER import browser client in Server Components
- NEVER import server client in Client Components

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS utility classes only — NO inline styles
- NO CSS modules
- Dark background theme (like the existing Netlify version)

