4. End every task with a TESTSCRIPT of max 5 points

## FORBIDDEN
- No pages/ directory — only app/
- No any types in TypeScript
- No hardcoded API keys or secrets
- No service_role / server-only Supabase secrets in the app
- Never delete code without explicit approval

## GIT COMMIT STANDARD (PERMANENT — ALWAYS FOLLOW)

Every commit MUST follow this format:

  vX.Y.Z type(scope): description

Types: feat | fix | style | refactor | docs | chore | perf

Examples:
  ✅ v0.2.15 feat(pwa): Add professional PWA setup with service worker
  ✅ v0.2.16 fix(manifest): Fix icon paths in manifest.json
  ✅ v0.2.17 style(layout): Update PWA meta tags in app/layout.tsx

RULES (NEVER BREAK):
- Version ALWAYS in package.json (MUST MATCH commit)
- Sequential versions (no skipping: 0.2.14 → 0.2.15 → 0.2.16)
- One logical change per commit (not everything at once)
- Git tags for releases: git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release message"
- Push after commit: git push origin main

WORKFLOW:
1. Update package.json version
2. Make changes & test locally (npm run dev)
3. Commit: git add . && git commit -m "vX.Y.Z type(scope): description"
4. Push: git push origin main
5. Tag: git tag -a vX.Y.Z -m "Release vX.Y.Z" && git push origin vX.Y.Z

Reference: 🔒 PolyCards — GIT COMMIT STANDARD (PERMANENT & BINDING)